article:
The article lists China's province-level divisions by gross domestic product
(GDP). Each province's GDP is listed in both the national currency renminbi
(CNÂ¥), and in US dollars, converted according to annual average exchange rates.
Historical figures and rankings, including purchasing power parity (PPP)
figures, are also given for main years since 1978. Figures for Hong Kong and
Macau, which are special administrative regions of the PRC but do not use the
same currency, are listed after the main list for comparative purposes. Official GDP figures for the Republic of China (ROC),
which governs Taiwan, Penghu, Kinmen and Matsu, are also included.

All the CNÂ¥ figures are from the National Bureau of Statistics of China. Annual PPP rates are taken from the International Monetary
Fund's World Economic Outlook databases.
